task_description: Facing the building to your North (approx. 2°), estimate the height of the main building in front of you in meters. Answer with one number and a short rationale.

reason: Moving to the right (10m) will provide a different perspective of the main building, helping me better observe its full height and estimate it more accurately relative to surrounding elements.
Based on typical multi-story office building heights (assuming 5 floors at approximately 4 meters per floor), I estimate the main building's height to be 20.0 meters.
